The paper deals with the problem of rate region in vector Gaussian multiple descriptions, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of quadratic distortion constraints suggests a focus on optimization (cs.LG) and the characterization of the rate region for the scalar Gaussian source suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
